    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe `context` field on [`vim.lsp.LocationOpts.OnList`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.LocationOpts.OnList) says that it's same as `ctx` from [`lsp-handler`] but it's not. It only passes `bufnr` and `method`:\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/10a3a854736895783aac9fd5dd86156f7ae25df1/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/buf.lua#L199\n\nBut the `ctx` from [`lsp-handler`] has additional fields: `client_id`, `params` and `version`.\n\n[`lsp-handler`]: https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#lsp-handler\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nIt's not specific to a language server, it's a mismatch between the documentation and what's implemented.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpected the `context` variable to have the same structure as `ctx`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1756+gc091bc3b9\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nany\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.2 (24C101)\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
